      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAD ABOUT MAGNUS (9) is a filly by Magnus out of Whitney on debut for the Hayes yard. She comes here off the back of a couple of jumpout wins and looks to have found an ideal maiden to kick off in. Should go close. CATTLE CAMP (3) is a first-starter by Per Incanto from Shanina who took out his most recent trial at Pakenham. Promising type who should be respected. BARK (1) is fresh from a spell of seven months and did hit the frame when last resuming at Pakenham Synthetic over 1000m, formerly with J Price. He can run well off a jumpout victory. NAR NAR GOON (2) was safely held when resuming last start over 1200m at Caulfield Heath, finishing eighth and beaten 6 lengths. This is easier and look for improvement. PATH OF HEROES (5) resumes having struggled when in the market on debut, he can do better this time around.",
